      <P><font face="Tahoma" color="#000000" size="4">Here at FCC people don't
      just receive, they give.&nbsp; The ministries of the church are carried
      out under the umbrella of a team.&nbsp; Many team leaders then represent
      those groups on the church's general board.&nbsp;</font> <font face="Tahoma" color="#000000" size="4">See
      where you could fit!</font></P>

      <p align="center">
        <font face="Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif" color="#ffffff" size="2">
     	   <img border="0" src="acts_of_kindness.jpg">
      	</font>
      </p>

      <P><font face="Arial" size="4" color="#000000">Social:&nbsp; </font><font face="Arial" color="#ffffff" size="3">This team is responsible for ministering to the needs of the congregation in times of stress or celebration.  For instance, they not only plan baby and wedding showers, but funeral dinners and meals for people recovering from illness.&nbsp;&nbsp;</font></P>

      <P><font face="Arial" size="4" color="#000000">Trustee:&nbsp;</font><font face="Arial" color="#ffffff" size="3">
      These folks take care of our physical building, grounds, and
      vehicle.&nbsp; They meet regularly for fellowship and &quot;fix it&quot;
      sessions.</font></P>

      <P><font face="Arial" size="4" color="#000000">Children Christian
      Education:&nbsp;</font><font face="Arial" color="#ffffff" size="3"> This
      department is actually composed of a variety of teams covering children's
      church, children's Sunday School, nursery, mid-week Kids Klub, Vacation
      Bible School, and all things kids.&nbsp; Many people have found their
      place helping with games and refreshments, or even teaching a lesson.</font></P>

      <P><font face="Arial" size="4" color="#000000">Worship:</font><font face="Arial" color="#ffffff" size="3">&nbsp;
      The worship team includes vocalists, instrumentalist, sound and graphic
      technicians.&nbsp; The group meets on a rotating basis&nbsp; twice weekly
      for practices.&nbsp;</font></P>

